{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/a-multiplatform-approach-to-mvi/","webpackCompilationHash":"abbcf1e1856f1bb11837","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"dfffa1f6-81eb-55d1-beb7-0f750032e6f4","html":"<p>As mobile applications have become massive pieces of code, we have always looked over architectures as a sole source of maintenance and making code easier for us. We have moved through cycles of architectures such as MVC, MVP, MVVM - MV* is a more appropriate acronym.</p>\n<p>But as our applications become more intuitive and faster, a requirement for reactive paradigm has always been felt. This is fulfilled in web through concepts of flux/redux and in mobile through MVI(same concept different target). And boy is it popular!\n<br></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/eda5b/mvi-multiplatform-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 98.73997709049254%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/01472/mvi-multiplatform-1.webp 240w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/222bd/mvi-multiplatform-1.webp 480w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/620b9/mvi-multiplatform-1.webp 960w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/28063/mvi-multiplatform-1.webp 1440w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/1b9e1/mvi-multiplatform-1.webp 1746w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/0783d/mvi-multiplatform-1.png 240w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/782f4/mvi-multiplatform-1.png 480w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/f570d/mvi-multiplatform-1.png 960w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/8d0ff/mvi-multiplatform-1.png 1440w,\n/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/eda5b/mvi-multiplatform-1.png 1746w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/d01911d91d7fdc176f9c285fa27e9803/f570d/mvi-multiplatform-1.png\"\n          alt=\"alt-text\"\n          title=\"alt-text\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<br></p>\n<p>MVI has pretty straightforward concepts</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Single source of truth</li>\n<li>State driven UI</li>\n<li>Side effects</li>\n<li>State produced through pure functions</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/d12c7/mvi-multiplatform-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72.30514096185739%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/01472/mvi-multiplatform-2.webp 240w,\n/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/222bd/mvi-multiplatform-2.webp 480w,\n/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/620b9/mvi-multiplatform-2.webp 960w,\n/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/23333/mvi-multiplatform-2.webp 1206w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/0783d/mvi-multiplatform-2.png 240w,\n/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/782f4/mvi-multiplatform-2.png 480w,\n/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/f570d/mvi-multiplatform-2.png 960w,\n/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/d12c7/mvi-multiplatform-2.png 1206w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/adc0aec9a3e8f24118518aca1a3501e1/f570d/mvi-multiplatform-2.png\"\n          alt=\"alt-text\"\n          title=\"alt-text\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>As is with other architectures, MVI also produces a lot of boilerplate code. You may need a core library to implement the base framework and then states, reducers, store have to be also implemented.</p>\n<p>This also means 2x work if you have Android + iOS using the same</p>\n<h3 id=\"enter-kotlin-multiplatform\"><a href=\"#enter-kotlin-multiplatform\" aria-label=\"enter kotlin multiplatform permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Enter Kotlin Multiplatform!</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"kotlin\"><pre class=\"language-kotlin\"><code class=\"language-kotlin\"><span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> counterStore <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">Store</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    reducer <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token operator\">::</span>counterReducer<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    state <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">CounterState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/a-multiplatform-approach-to-mvi/","tagSlugs":["/tag/multiplatform/","/tag/kotlin/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-08-19T22:40:32.169Z","description":"As mobile applications have become massive pieces of code, we have always looked over architectures as a sole source of maintenance and making code easier for us. We have moved through cycles of architectures such as MVC, MVP, MVVM - MV* is a more appropriate acronym.","tags":["Multiplatform","Kotlin"],"title":"A Multiplatform approach to MVI"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/a-multiplatform-approach-to-mvi/"}}}